backpack.title: Finale
backpack.titleText: All of your choices in one spot!

rows.title: Hello!
rows.titleText: And welcome to Ozzie's Inflation Chart! This is a complete chart that will assess you on your various inflation preferences so others can see what you do and do not enjoy. I won't occupy too much of your time, so...

rows.title: Types
rows.titleText: You can't be a balloon without something to fill up with? The four choices below will open up more preferences for you!

objects.title: Gas
objects.text: For the balloon lighter than a feather~

objects.title: Liquid
objects.text: For the thirsty guzzler~

objects.title: Solid
objects.text: For the hungry glutton~

objects.title: Other
objects.text: For the balloon who prefers other methods~

objects.title: Air
objects.text: Everyone's gas go-to!

objects.title: Helium
objects.text: It makes you float!

objects.title: Bodily Gas
objects.text: Not everyone's preference, but certainly someone's~

objects.title: Other Gases
objects.text: Not every option can be listed out individually, so this lumps everything else together!

objects.title: Water
objects.text: Water is the driving force behind pretty much all life on Earth!

objects.title: Soda
objects.text: Sugary, fizzy, delicious, and very cheap!

objects.title: Juice
objects.text: Be warned that certain juices might give you a distinct hue!

objects.title: (Whipped) Cream
objects.text: Straight from the tub or straight from the can!

objects.title: Smoothie or Blended
objects.text: No better way to get all of your nutrients than with a smoothie!

objects.title: Other Liquids
objects.text: Not every option can be listed out individually, so this lumps everything else together!

objects.title: Food
objects.text: Food is always good, it's no wonder you want to stuff your face!

objects.title: Slime
objects.text: Slime creatures make the best ballooning material!

objects.title: Other Solids
objects.text: Not every option can be listed out individually, so this lumps everything else together!

objects.title: Magic, Curses, or Potions
objects.text: Beware of stray curses and dangerous potions, it could turn out very bad (or good) for you!

objects.title: Automata, Tech, or Machinery
objects.text: "Inflation can always be optimized!" - Henry Ford, probably

objects.title: Latex, Rubber, or Bodysuit
objects.text: It may not be you inflating, but it's just as stimulating!

objects.title: Drone, Hypnosis, or Mental Stimulation
objects.text: Isn't it easy to just give in?~

objects.title: Teasing, Praise, or Vocal Stimulation
objects.text: Good boy, getting so big!~

objects.title: Other Options
objects.text: Not every option can be listed out individually, so this lumps everything else together!

rows.title: Position
rows.titleText: Every balloon has preferences, and whether or not they're an inflator or an inflatee is one of them!

objects.title: Only Inflatee
objects.text: You only like to be inflated, and/or the thought of inflating others turns you away.

objects.title: Preferred Inflatee
objects.text: Being inflated is your preference, but you don't mind inflating others every once in a while.

objects.title: Lean Inflatee
objects.text: You certainly don't mind inflating others, but you enjoy being inflated more.

objects.title: Both
objects.text: You don't mind or care about being either an inflator or an inflatee.

objects.title: Lean Inflator
objects.text: You certainly don't mind being inflated, but you enjoy inflating others more.

objects.title: Preferred Inflator
objects.text: Inflating others is your preference, but you don't mind being inflated every once in a while.

objects.title: Only Inflator
objects.text: You only like to inflate others, and/or the thought of being inflated turns you away.

rows.title: Shapes
rows.titleText: Balloons don't always fill up the same way, so here's where you can decide what you like the most!

objects.title: Perfect Sphere
objects.text: The all around well-rounded balloon!

objects.title: Belly Bloat
objects.text: When the belly is all you want attention for!

objects.title: Hourglass
objects.text: Just as it says, inflation of the breasts and the butt!

objects.title: Top Heavy
objects.text: Also known as breast inflation!

objects.title: Bottom Heavy
objects.text: Also known as butt inflation, though can also include the thighs!

objects.title: Muscles Only
objects.text: Inflation only of big muscle groups for the perfect bodybuilder figure!

rows.title: Size
rows.titleText: Every balloon has a preference on how big they can get, and you are no different! Belly measurements are given as a reference as well.

objects.title: Small Bump
objects.text:
Barely noticeable and somewhat easily hidden under large hoodies and jackets.
Belly: up to 12 inches in diameter

objects.title: Volleyball
objects.text:
You're beginning to get too large for clothes to cover yourself up easily, but it's not too extreme yet!
Belly: 1 to 2 feet in diameter

objects.title: Yoga Ball
objects.text:
Now people are starting to stare at how big you've become~
Belly: 2 to 4 feet in diameter

objects.title: Furniture
objects.text:
Things are starting to get unruly, but it's nothing you can't handle!
Belly: 4 to 15 feet in diameter

objects.title: Living Room
objects.text:
You've begun to fill the room you're in...
Belly: 15 to 50 feet in diameter

objects.title: House
objects.text:
...and now you're bigger than the house itself!~
Belly: 50 to 150 feet in diameter

objects.title: Neighborhood
objects.text:
One house wasn't enough, you need to be bigger than multiple!
Belly: 150 to 500 feet in diameter

objects.title: Skyscraper
objects.text:
Reach for the sky, you might be able to touch it!
Belly: 500 feet to 0.25 mile in diameter

objects.title: City
objects.text:
It's a bird! It's a plane! No, it's a blimp!~
Belly: 0.25 to 25 miles in diameter

objects.title: Country
objects.text:
Breaking news: massive blimp growing out of control!
Belly: 25 to 250 miles in diameter

objects.title: Continental
objects.text:
Will you ever stop growing?~
Belly: 250 to 2,500 miles

objects.title: Planetary
objects.text:
Now look at you, you're causing an eclipse, you big balloon~
Belly: 2,500 to 250,000 miles

objects.title: Stellar
objects.text:
You're blotting out the Sun now? You're massive~
Belly: 250,000 miles to 1 lightyear

objects.title: Interplanetary
objects.text:
And you're still growing bigger!
Belly: 1 to 1,000 lightyears

objects.title: Interstellar
objects.text:
Though it would be in your best interest to stop...
Belly: 1,000 to 1,000,000 lightyears

objects.title: Cosmos
objects.text:
You're getting too huge!~
Belly: 1,000,000 to 1,000,000,000 lightyears

objects.title: Universe
objects.text:
You might be too big now...!
Belly: 1,000,000,000 to 93,000,000,000 lightyears

objects.title: Infinite
objects.text:
?!~
Belly: ???
